ESSID VS. BSSID
ESSID : NAME OF THE WIFI/ CONNECTION NAME (we can have same essid, two hostspots with name network123)
BSSID : MAC ADDRESS OF THE ACCESSPOINT/ ROUTER	(unique, two routers can never have same bssid)

