installing virt-manager in ubuntu	#qemu,virtual machine manager, kvm
sudo apt-get install qemu-kvm qemu virt-manager virt-viewer libvirt-bin
**************NOTE: LOG OUT AND LOG IN REQUIRED TO WORK TO MAKE THE VIRT-VIEWER WORK.******
>>	Location of the storage images:	/var/lib/libvirt/images/
error correction:
if it says cannot read image from the disk, just edit the file below
sudo nano /etc/libvirt/qemu.conf
	>> and uncomment the line 
			user=root
			group=root
just save the file.
And restart the libvirtd service as>> 
systemctl restart libvirtd
