___________________________________________________________________
ENABLING REPOS IN YUM FROM CD/DVD/ISO >> <path-of-os-file>

$cd /etc/yum.repos.d/
$ls
$ls
CentOS-Base.repo  CentOS-Debuginfo.repo  CentOS-Media.repo    CentOS-Vault.repo
CentOS-CR.repo    CentOS-fasttrack.repo  CentOS-Sources.repo
$sudo nano CentOS-Media.repo
#now just change the value of the enabled to 1.
#and also add the <path-of-os-file> to the list of sources under > {baseurl=}
save and exit.
$sudo yum --disablerepo=\* --enablerepo=media install <package-name>	 ##this works fine but replace media with the identifier of repo.
									## identifier is the string inside [] in repo file.
$sudo yum --enablerepo=media install <package-name> ##this does not work at all
________________________________
ANOTHER METHOD (MUCH SIMPLE)
do the editing of the CentOS-Media.repo like above.
$sudo nautilus /etc/yum.repos.d/
move all the repo files except the CentOS-Media.repo to the backup folder.
now you can simply install directly with enabling disabling repos.
$sudo yum install bind
$sudo yum install vnc

