___________________________________________
grep: grep -A 5 <text>		>> prints 5 lines after the match of the found_word.
grep -i <text>	  >> ignores the case sensitive for the <text>(shows_all_combinations)
grep -E <special_character>	>> search for the chars such as ? , + , {} , () and |
grep -v <text>		>>search for the lines not containing <text>
grep -n <text>		>>shows the line number
grep --line-number <text>		^^

{if some lines are coming as -----;
	it means that there are other lines but with case sensitive searched text}

grep "^Car"	>> this will show only the lines starting with word Car
grep "Car$"	>> this will search with lines ending with Car
grep "..cept"	>> this will search for accept and except and other words like that..
grep t[wo]o	>> will search for two and too both the words and other words like that...
grep "[^c]ode"	>> will seach for words *ode except code. like mode, pode, fode
grep "^[A-Z]"  	>> all lines starting with capital words
grep "\(grouping\)"
grep "\-X"	>> search for -X in the lines
